A teenage girl has become the eighth Tibetan child to set herself alight to protest against Chinese rule over ethnic Tibetan areas, rights groups said today.

Wangchen Kyi, 16, self-immolated and died in western Qinghai province on Sunday evening.

Campaign group Free Tibet reported that her final words were: 'Long live His Holiness the Dalai Lama, long live the Tibetan People'. The London-based organisation said the girl was 16 and and leaves behind her parents and two sisters.

