The International Campaign for Tibet, another Tibet awareness organisation, said Wangchen set herself on fire on the nomadic grasslands of Zeku county, where she was later cremated.

She was on holiday from Tsekog County Second National Middle School in eastern Tibet at the time of her protest. Authorities confirmed the self-immolation today.

The local community claimed her body and an estimated three thousand local people attended her cremation service at around midnight.

